      "name": "TARGET_multicell_capacity",
      "statement": "\u230aTARGET/(e\u00b7p)\u230b = 1911. If each e\u00b7p-cell pays one multi-tier layer of \u2264K_cap highs, then \u22644146870 highs are payable against residual TARGET. This is NOT a proof that A_SP may use TARGET multi-cells (A_SP\u2264t\u00b7p is the single-cell goal); it bounds how far layered multi-tier can go if charged to TARGET.",
      "status": "PROVED_ARITHMETIC"
    },
    "ep_budget": {
      "deployed": {
        "K_cap": 2170,
        "R_max": 70,
        "e": 67472,
        "side_radix": 67270,
        "slack": 202
      },
      "name": "single_ep_side_mark_budget",
      "proof": [
        "Encode k = (\u03c4\u00b7\u230an/e\u230b + local)\u00b7\u230an/e\u230b + \u03b9 \u2208 [0, R\u00b7floor\u00b2).",
        "Need k < e to pair with \u03b4\u2208F_p as (k mod e is free if k<e; or (k,\u03b4)).",
        "R=70: 70\u00b731\u00b731=67270\u226467472. R=71: 71\u00b731\u00b731=68231>e.",
        "This is why R_max=70 is forced for one e\u00b7p side cell with \u03b9."
      ],
      "statement": "Side mark (\u03c4, local, \u03b9, \u03b4) with \u03c4<R, local<\u230an/e\u230b, \u03b9<\u230an/e\u230b, \u03b4\u2208F_p injects into [e]\u00d7F_p (via mixed radix on first three coords) iff R\u00b7\u230an/e\u230b\u00b7\u230an/e\u230b \u2264 e. Deployed: R_max=70 gives 67270 \u2264 e=67472 (slack 202). Hence a single e\u00b7p cell supports at most R_max=70 tiers and |H|\u2264K_cap=2170 (or |H|\u2264K_MAX=2176 if local slots are fully used without the R\u00b7floor packing gap).",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "local_neg": {
      "name": "local_overflow_marks_collide",
      "statement": "Natural local overflow marks (c0U,\u03b4), (c0U,c0V), (minU mod e, \u03b4), (minU, c0U), (sumU mod e, \u03b4) fail injectivity on overflow pairs in toys. No local e\u00b7p replacement for \u03bc_over found.",
      "status": "BANKED_NEGATIVE"
    },
    "mu_over": {
      "name": "mu_over_enum_conditional_ep",
      "proof": [
        "v39 mixed-radix rank."
      ],
      "statement": "Order overflow pairs lex; rank i; \u03bc_over=(i mod e, \u230ai/e\u230b) injective. If N_over \u2264 e\u00b7p then \u03bc_over lands in [e]\u00d7F_p (v39).",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "no_multilayer": {
      "name": "no_second_multitier_layer_in_one_ep",
      "proof": [
        "2\u00b767270=134540 > e=67472."
      ],
      "statement": "\u039b full multi-tier layers each using radix 67270 need \u039b\u00b767270 \u2264 e to share one e\u00b7p cell with \u03b9. Only \u039b=1 works (67270\u2264e < 2\u00b767270).",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "pigeon": {
      "name": "pigeonhole_overflow_size",
      "proof": [
        "Capacity of R_max tiers \u2264 R_max\u00b7\u230an/e\u230b = K_cap matched highs.",
        "Pigeonhole: unmatched \u2265 |H| \u2212 capacity."
      ],
      "statement": "Any matching schedule with capacity K_cap=2170 (R_max tiers \u00d7 \u2264\u230an/e\u230b highs/tier) leaves at least max(0, |H|\u2212K_cap) highs unmatched. When a packing of size min(|H|,K_cap) exists, multi-tier can achieve equality |H_over|=max(0,|H|\u2212K_cap).",
      "status": "PROVED"
    }
  },
